56.2	Terry_Bradshaw	Terry Bradshaw	Terry Paxton Bradshaw (born September 2, 1948) is a former American football quarterback with the Pittsburgh Steelers in the National Football League (NFL). He is currently a TV analyst and co-host of Fox NFL Sunday. He played 14 seasons with Pittsburgh, won four Super Bowl titles in a six-year period , becoming the first quarterback to win three and four Super Bowls, and led the Steelers to eight AFC Central championships. He was inducted into the Pro Football Hall of Fame in 1989, his first year of eligibility.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b2/Terry_Bradshaw.jpg/220px-Terry_Bradshaw.jpg
